===Etymology===
From Old English ''[[vois]]'', ''[[voys]]'' < Old French ''[[vois]]'', ''[[voiz]]'', French ''[[voix]]'' < Latin ''[[vox]]'', ''[[vocis]]'', akin to Sanskrit [[वच्]] (to say, to speak) and German ''[[erwähnen]]'' (to mention). Compare [[advocate]], [[advowson]], [[avouch]], [[convoke]], [[epic]], [[vocal]], [[vouch]], [[vowel]].

